Quote:  Two migra-[123]tory cuckoos (the Cuculus fasciatus, Forst.), called kohaperoa, or koekoia, and a very small and beautiful kind (the Cuculus nitems of the same author), called by the natives pipiwawaroa - which appear on the coast at Christmas - mark the period of the first potato-harvest. <i>ibid.</i> 2/193 40. <i>Eudynamys taitensis</i>. ... Kohaperoa of the natives. <i>Yate</i>. `Koheperoa', from a specimen. <i>Miss Stone</i>. Kohapiroa. <i>Polack? </i>Koekoia of the natives.<i>

